<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Dower" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Dower,</orth> subst. 1) the property which a woman brings to her husband in marriage: <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.1.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 1, 54</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mm 1.2.154" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 2, 154</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.3.151" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 3, 151</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 4.4.19" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 5.3.328" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 328</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.1.44" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 1, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.5.46" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 45</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 45</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 45</bibl><lb />2) that which a widow possesses after the death of her husband: <bibl n="shak. shr 2.345" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 345</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 2.345" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 345</bibl> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.2.117" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 117</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.4.45" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.2.72" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 2, 72</bibl>.
<lb />3) any gift? <cit><quote>If this suit lay in Bianca's d., how quickly should you speed!</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 4.1.108" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 1, 108</bibl></cit> (or indeed == marriage-portion? Qq and most M. Edd. <emph>power</emph>).
